1
00:00:10,270 --> 00:00:11,590
[gentle dreamy music plays]

2
00:00:11,670 --> 00:00:14,710
[Sam cheerfully] Okay! Whoo!

3
00:00:15,270 --> 00:00:17,270
[Rosie and Sam laughing]

4
00:00:19,950 --> 00:00:21,630
- [Sam] Come on.
- [Rosie] No!

5
00:00:21,710 --> 00:00:22,830
[both laugh]

6
00:00:22,910 --> 00:00:24,230
[Sam] Why not? It's lovely.

7
00:00:24,910 --> 00:00:26,550
[Sam shivers and laughs]

8
00:00:26,630 --> 00:00:29,190
- [laughs] No! No.
- [water splashes]

9
00:00:29,950 --> 00:00:31,790
I could teach you to swim if you want.

10
00:00:31,870 --> 00:00:34,710
[chuckles] It's against the rules.

11
00:00:34,790 --> 00:00:37,550
What? "Thou shalt not front crawl"?

12
00:00:37,630 --> 00:00:38,710
[both laugh]

13
00:00:38,790 --> 00:00:41,110
Come on, get out. You must be freezing.

14
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:44,190
[grunts]

15
00:00:46,270 --> 00:00:47,470
[both laugh]

16
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:54,990
[both breathe heavily]

17
00:01:06,030 --> 00:01:08,310
What's that? A birthday?

18
00:01:08,390 --> 00:01:11,070
Um… [clears throat] I'll tell you one day.

19
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:31,230
So, um…

20
00:01:32,310 --> 00:01:34,230
what time do you have to get back?

21
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:36,790
I'm not.

22
00:01:38,790 --> 00:01:40,150
Oh, you're not going back?

23
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:44,790
Okay, so you're just gonna stay
here in the woods, then?

24
00:01:46,310 --> 00:01:47,670
Hide with me?

25
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:53,030
How will we pass the time?

26
00:02:15,310 --> 00:02:17,310
How's that? The right length?

27
00:02:17,390 --> 00:02:20,550
[Adam] Uh… Yep. Yeah, I think so.

28
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:22,190
I'll just finish these.

29
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:26,550
My father used to say, 

30
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:29,270
"Becoming a leader's
like a coat you get used to."

31
00:02:30,950 --> 00:02:34,230
"Heavy on the shoulders, 
tight around the chest."

32
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:38,190
A higher calling, Brother Adam.

33
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:41,110
[Mrs. Phillips] It's not the suit, 

34
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:43,070
but the soul within it.

35
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,470
And yours is pristine.

36
00:02:45,550 --> 00:02:46,950
[tense ethereal music plays]

37
00:02:57,270 --> 00:02:58,750
And smile.

38
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:02,510
[shutter clicks]

39
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:06,990
[somber theme music plays]

40
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:14,550
[chattering indistinctly]

41
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:22,310
[ominous music plays]

42
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:26,150
[siren whoops]

43
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:32,470
[siren whoops twice]

44
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:36,710
Excuse me. Excuse me.

45
00:03:36,790 --> 00:03:39,110
This number eight? The Harrisons'?

46
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:43,110
We're looking for an escaped prisoner.

47
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:46,670
Do you have any information?
Any sightings?

48
00:03:51,510 --> 00:03:54,150
I'm sorry, I've never seen him before.
I can't help you.

49
00:03:58,230 --> 00:04:00,910
And your husband, Adam Harrison?

50
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,430
- [workers yell indistinctly]
- [saw whirs]

51
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:10,110
The guy's behind on the first phase.
We really need to get a move on.

52
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,830
[suspenseful music plays]

53
00:04:19,470 --> 00:04:20,430
[saws whirring]

54
00:04:22,110 --> 00:04:23,950
[man in distance] Gotta reverse it first!

55
00:04:36,470 --> 00:04:39,390
Once the other shipment's in, 
we'll get that identified.

56
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:41,790
- Sam!
- [saw whirs loudly]

57
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,830
Sam! Sam!

58
00:04:44,590 --> 00:04:45,830
[saw stops whirring]

59
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:48,310
Rosie, what's going on?

60
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:50,510
The police are coming.
They're looking for Sam.

61
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:53,950
We need to hide you.

62
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:03,510
[Sam] Thanks.

63
00:05:05,470 --> 00:05:06,470
For lying for me.

64
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:11,190
We don't like the police.

65
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:13,750
God's judgment is the only righteous one.

66
00:05:19,470 --> 00:05:20,510
Not here.

67
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:29,110
[tense music plays]

68
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:32,630
- [cop] Thanks for your time, Mr. Harrison.
- Of course.

69
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:34,470
[cop] Let us know
if you see or hear anything.

70
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:35,630
[engine starts]

71
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:42,110
[car recedes into distance]

72
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:44,670
It's all clear.

73
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,350
They're gone.

74
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:52,030
I'm grateful. Thank you.

75
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:53,990
[gentle intriguing music plays]

76
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:56,870
Look, I-- I don't take it for granted
what you're doing.

77
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,750
Well, we don't trust the police.

78
00:06:01,390 --> 00:06:03,790
Yeah, uh, Rosie was explaining.

79
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:10,710
Anyway, I better get back to work.

80
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:13,190
- Thanks.
- Mmm.

81
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:23,550
Rosie, the police are saying
that he's-- he's on the run.

82
00:06:24,470 --> 00:06:26,230
He's an escaped prisoner.

83
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:28,710
Okay.

84
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:33,710
Is it?

85
00:06:35,910 --> 00:06:38,630
I-- I don't know what he's done.
I don't know what this changes.

86
00:06:38,710 --> 00:06:39,750
It doesn't.

87
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:41,990
It doesn't change anything.

88
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,750
He's one of us now.

89
00:06:54,590 --> 00:06:56,590
[melancholic music plays]

90
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:03,190
[telephone rings]

91
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:09,950
[beeps]

92
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:11,350
[Isaac] Hello?

93
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:13,470
Anthony, is that you?

94
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:18,670
Anthony, please, just get your mum.
It's really important, okay?

95
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,590
- Anthony, can you hear--
- [phone beeps]

96
00:07:24,030 --> 00:07:25,190
Was that him?

97
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:28,990
Hmm?

98
00:07:29,070 --> 00:07:31,230
[sternly] Anthony, was that Daddy again?

99
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:41,510
[somber music plays]

100
00:07:44,710 --> 00:07:46,710
[vehicles whir and beep]

101
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:48,990
[Sam] Just come out with it.

102
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:51,670
[men chatter in yard]

103
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,950
You can ask me.

104
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:57,630
Anything.

105
00:07:57,710 --> 00:07:58,990
I don't need to.

106
00:08:01,030 --> 00:08:01,870
No?

107
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:07,230
I mean, it's-- it's clear
the cops have got in your head.

108
00:08:16,590 --> 00:08:19,030
Come on, you can't do this to me.
Come on, it's not fair.

109
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:25,550
You-- You, uh…

110
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:29,550
You said the baptism
was a clean slate, right?

111
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:34,110
- Adam, but if it's not, then--
- It is.

112
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:37,710
It is.

113
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:39,950
Yeah?

114
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:42,789
[chuckles]

115
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:57,390
So, who called the police?

116
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:03,550
My brother, Isaac.

117
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,630
[music intensifies]

118
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:14,790
[footsteps approaching]

119
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:33,270
[car approaches]

120
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,310
[engine stops]

121
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:48,350
[women and children chatter nearby]

122
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:55,910
Sorry about the sawdust, Mr. Phillips.

123
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:57,990
"Is not this the carpenter's son?"

124
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:02,790
Ah, Matthew, 13:55.

125
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:07,430
A meeting every evening, two on a Sunday.
Need more than one set.

126
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:08,790
One more thing.

127
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:15,510
[objects clatter softly]

128
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:22,030
[tense ethereal music plays]

129
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:23,310
[clattering continues]

130
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:30,590
Here we are.

131
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,310
[door closes]

132
00:10:36,350 --> 00:10:37,310
The Good Book.

133
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:43,150
A new chapter, Sam.

134
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:49,230
[Mr. Phillips] We welcome
our new brother, Sam.

135
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:50,550
Thank you.

136
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,190
[congregation] Welcome, Sam.

137
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:56,230
[Mr. Phillips] Baptized and born again
in Jesus Christ!

138
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:58,270
[congregation] Hallelujah!

139
00:10:58,350 --> 00:11:00,750
We invite him to take his first communion.

140
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:03,390
[sweeping music plays]

141
00:11:05,590 --> 00:11:10,150
We break this bread
to share in the body of Christ.

142
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:37,550
Though we are many, we are one.

143
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:39,870
[congregation] We all share in one bread.

144
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:41,430
[door opens briskly]

145
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:45,510
[softly] Mrs. Phillips, 
you need to come now.

146
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:46,910
[scattered whispering]

147
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:49,270
Brother Adam.

148
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:56,790
[congregation chatters indistinctly]

149
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:02,470
Rosie, I'm needed.

150
00:12:02,550 --> 00:12:04,030
Me and Mr. Phillips.

151
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,710
Mrs. Dawson's about to pass.

152
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:09,510
It's my duty to shepherd her soul.

153
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:15,710
Sam.

154
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:16,790
Yeah?

155
00:12:17,430 --> 00:12:19,470
Could you drop these two home for me?

156
00:12:19,550 --> 00:12:21,150
Of course. No problem.

157
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:25,390
Mummy? Mummy, can I go
to tea at Anthony's?

158
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:29,150
- It's not really up to me, darling.
- [Noah cries]

159
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:32,150
What's one more?

160
00:12:33,710 --> 00:12:36,390
You know, I never get this. Ever.

161
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:37,550
A night to myself.

162
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:41,430
There's always cleaning, 
cooking, Grace, meetings.

163
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:44,310
I barely have a moment
to think about what I want to do.

164
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:46,110
And what do you want to do?

165
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:49,310
[door opens]

166
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,470
[door closes]

167
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:53,950
I want to go out.

168
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,150
[Sam chuckles]

169
00:12:56,990 --> 00:12:58,470
[Rosie laughs]

170
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,870
[geese honk]

171
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:02,950
["Run Away" by Sarah Jarosz plays]

172
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:09,950
♪ Follow me
Down through the cotton fields ♪

173
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:14,350
♪ Moon shadow shine bright
The way you will ♪

174
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:18,110
♪ Lead us down a road where no one goes ♪

175
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:21,750
♪ We can run away ♪

176
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:27,070
♪ Come take my hand
While I'm waiting here ♪

177
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:31,790
♪ Get away from it all
And find what's real ♪

178
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:35,390
♪ If we don't get out now
The chance won't reappear ♪

179
00:13:35,470 --> 00:13:38,870
♪ We can run away ♪

180
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:47,550
♪ Hold me tight and don't let go… ♪

181
00:13:48,230 --> 00:13:51,870
[Sam] And a large chicken kebab
and chips, please.

182
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:53,750
You're not gonna have this?

183
00:13:53,830 --> 00:13:55,670
- [laughs] No.
- [laughs]

184
00:13:59,230 --> 00:14:00,350
Garlic.

185
00:14:00,430 --> 00:14:02,430
[both laugh]

186
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,950
Never had this.

187
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:06,590
Food like this.

188
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,870
It's nice.

189
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:15,510
[door chimes open]

190
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:17,910
- [siren wails in distance]
- [Sam clears throat]

191
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:20,590
[man] What can I get you guys?

192
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:23,070
[woman] Two, uh… Two large number threes.

193
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,390
[man] You want sauce?

194
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:26,990
[customer and employee
continue indistinctly]

195
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:28,470
Do you want children?

196
00:14:30,190 --> 00:14:31,550
I always did.

197
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:35,030
Always saw myself with a large family.

198
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:38,590
Babies, toddlers crawling
around everywhere.

199
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:42,350
Uh…

200
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:44,550
I mean, yeah. [chuckles]

201
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:48,190
Yeah, I used to think about it
all the time when I was inside.

202
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:51,070
Things I thought I'd never have, you know?

203
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:53,270
A house and…

204
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:57,070
wife and kids.

205
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:59,670
I used to talk about it in Group.

206
00:15:00,310 --> 00:15:02,070
The chances are, 
if you've had shit parents, 

207
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:04,510
you're probably gonna be
a shit parent yourself.

208
00:15:05,150 --> 00:15:07,310
So they try to teach you to…

209
00:15:08,190 --> 00:15:09,430
make it different.

210
00:15:09,510 --> 00:15:11,510
[tender music plays]

211
00:15:11,590 --> 00:15:13,870
The rest of the time you're banged up.

212
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:18,670
The only thing you really learn
is how not to get your head kicked in.

213
00:15:22,950 --> 00:15:25,230
Even when you're asleep, 
you have to have one eye open.

214
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:27,510
And the noise, fucking hell.

215
00:15:27,590 --> 00:15:29,030
And the smell.

216
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:31,630
And the sweat.

217
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,030
And fear.

218
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:39,550
[breath trembles]

219
00:15:42,030 --> 00:15:44,190
I just want some peace, Rosie.

220
00:15:56,110 --> 00:15:57,430
[wheezing]

221
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:00,510
[woman] I can feel Him.

222
00:16:00,590 --> 00:16:03,470
God all-seeing, all-knowing, 
in this very room.

223
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:07,910
And it's your honor
to help her to cross over.

224
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:10,150
[Adam exhales nervously]

225
00:16:10,230 --> 00:16:12,230
[anxious ethereal music plays]

226
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:17,350
[exhales]

227
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:24,710
[Mr. Phillips taps fingers]

228
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:27,950
[Adam] Father…

229
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,750
your precious servant
is nearing her time on…

230
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:36,310
the end of her time on our…

231
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,670
on this earth.

232
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,470
[music intensifies]

233
00:16:48,830 --> 00:16:53,190
[dishes clatter softly]

234
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:04,270
[anxious music swells]

235
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:23,670
[Rosie] Can I try it?

236
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,670
- What?
- Your…

237
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:30,470
The lipstick.

238
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,070
It's gloss.

239
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:34,670
And no.

240
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:36,510
Please… [chuckles nervously] …it's just…

241
00:17:37,870 --> 00:17:39,270
I've never worn it before.

242
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:03,910
Yeah. Yeah, that actually suits you.

243
00:18:03,990 --> 00:18:05,230
[both chuckle]

244
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:07,710
Thank you.

245
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:14,310
[Adam] I stand before you, 

246
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:17,190
your pure and holy servant…

247
00:18:19,150 --> 00:18:20,910
and I offer you this soul.

248
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:23,310
And I…

249
00:18:23,390 --> 00:18:25,390
[anxious music plays]

250
00:18:26,030 --> 00:18:28,390
Hey, I can see clearly
how pathetic you are.

251
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:31,910
Pose and preach all you want.
I know how weak you are.

252
00:18:31,990 --> 00:18:33,670
[music intensifies]

253
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:37,670
I can't. I can't. I can't.
I'm not the right shepherd.

254
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,310
What's wrong with you, man? Step up.

255
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:41,630
Please! She deserves better.

256
00:18:41,710 --> 00:18:42,670
[woman] Mr. Phillips.

257
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,870
- Do your job.
- Please, she deserves better than this.

258
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:46,710
Entrust this woman into God.

259
00:18:46,790 --> 00:18:48,310
He sees into my soul.

260
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:51,390
Mr. Phillips. Mr. Phillips, it's time.

261
00:18:53,670 --> 00:18:55,150
[ominous music plays]

262
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:59,070
[Mr. Phillips] Into Your hands, 
O Lord, we commend her spirit.

263
00:19:00,110 --> 00:19:02,190
Deliver her now from every sorrow, 

264
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:04,590
and grant her eternal rest.

265
00:19:05,430 --> 00:19:06,910
Through Christ our Lord.

266
00:19:08,030 --> 00:19:09,390
Amen. [audio fades]

267
00:19:11,990 --> 00:19:13,990
[uneasy music plays]

268
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:17,510
[door opens and closes]

269
00:19:21,510 --> 00:19:22,350
What's that?

270
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,750
I thought it looked nice.

271
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:30,910
You don't need that.

272
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:33,590
To… be that.

273
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:39,030
I'm sorry. Uh…

274
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:52,110
[uneasy music intensifies]

275
00:19:58,710 --> 00:20:00,230
[door chimes open]

276
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:02,550
[door closes]

277
00:20:09,430 --> 00:20:10,710
[sirens wail]

278
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:12,430
- [exclaims]
- For fuck's sake, Rosie.

279
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:15,750
Put your arm around me, okay?
We're gonna walk back to the van.

280
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:18,150
- They're not looking for a couple.
- [Rosie gasps]

281
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:20,990
[alarm chirps, doors unlock]

282
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:29,070
- We need to go.
- [sniffs]

283
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:31,230
I need to pick up Grace.

284
00:20:37,590 --> 00:20:39,390
I'm sorry for running off.

285
00:20:41,230 --> 00:20:42,910
And getting angry.

286
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,870
I should have said no to going out.

287
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:46,990
I can't do it. It's just too dangerous.

288
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,550
It's my fault. I'm sorry.

289
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,190
Rosie, you don't have to…

290
00:20:53,110 --> 00:20:56,190
I want more than anything
to make a fresh start.

291
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:59,350
But we can't do it, not out here.

292
00:20:59,430 --> 00:21:01,390
Always waiting for a hand on my shoulder.

293
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:02,870
We can't stay and be together.

294
00:21:03,870 --> 00:21:04,790
I'm married to Adam.

295
00:21:04,870 --> 00:21:07,230
Marriages end. Divorce him.

296
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:12,830
Only men can get a divorce
in the Fellowship.

297
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:15,870
I can't leave Adam
unless I leave the community.

298
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:19,550
- We'll find a way.
- How?

299
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:23,550
We can't make it work if we stay.

300
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:26,350
I have a husband.

301
00:21:26,430 --> 00:21:27,910
[somber music plays]

302
00:21:41,870 --> 00:21:42,910
[seatbelt clicks]

303
00:22:19,950 --> 00:22:21,470
[parking brake whirs]

304
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:26,670
[cell phone chimes]

305
00:22:33,470 --> 00:22:34,550
[engine stops]

306
00:22:54,990 --> 00:22:57,270
I saw the light from the fire.

307
00:23:00,230 --> 00:23:01,270
Is it okay if I join you?

308
00:23:07,710 --> 00:23:10,270
How was it? With the, um…

309
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:11,790
Uh, with the old lady?

310
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:17,430
It was, um…

311
00:23:26,230 --> 00:23:27,830
terrible. I'm…

312
00:23:29,710 --> 00:23:31,790
I couldn't do it. I-- I couldn't…

313
00:23:33,470 --> 00:23:36,270
I couldn't deliver her soul.
I'm-- I'm not the…

314
00:23:36,910 --> 00:23:38,630
I'm not the right man.

315
00:23:39,230 --> 00:23:40,750
Listen, I'm sure you did your best.

316
00:23:40,830 --> 00:23:42,830
It's not enough.
I am meant to be a leader.

317
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:50,270
A-- A-- A vessel
of God's glory and truth and, uh…

318
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:51,990
[dark brooding music plays]

319
00:23:52,070 --> 00:23:53,310
With a clean heart.

320
00:23:53,390 --> 00:23:55,550
And I'm not… I'm-- I'm not…

321
00:23:58,790 --> 00:24:01,790
I'm not the righteous man everyone…

322
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:08,470
I'm lost and…

323
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:14,470
stained.

324
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:22,030
You know what your problem is, Adam?

325
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:26,430
You think far too much.

326
00:24:26,510 --> 00:24:27,630
[chuckles softly]

327
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:30,310
It can't be good for you.

328
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:34,910
You are far more powerful
than you realize.

329
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:45,590
[music intensifies]

330
00:25:11,710 --> 00:25:13,110
[Adam's breath catches]

331
00:25:22,830 --> 00:25:24,310
[zipper unzips]

332
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:52,190
[music peaks and fades]

333
00:25:56,310 --> 00:25:58,310
[vehicle approaches outside]

334
00:26:03,670 --> 00:26:04,750
[engine shuts off]

335
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:06,870
[vehicle door opens and closes]

336
00:26:09,870 --> 00:26:11,190
[house door opens]

337
00:26:12,190 --> 00:26:13,430
[door shuts heavily]

338
00:26:13,510 --> 00:26:14,750
[footsteps approach]

339
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,750
How was it with Mrs. Dawson?

340
00:26:34,550 --> 00:26:36,390
It was-- It was very peaceful.

341
00:26:38,030 --> 00:26:39,230
How about you?

342
00:26:40,190 --> 00:26:41,830
Just a quiet night in.

343
00:27:15,950 --> 00:27:17,270
[Adam sighs]

344
00:27:21,150 --> 00:27:22,910
[breath trembles]

345
00:27:22,990 --> 00:27:25,350
[telephone rings]

346
00:27:27,950 --> 00:27:29,510
- [beeps]
- Hello.

347
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:31,430
[Isaac] Hey. Uh, hey, Adam, it's me.

348
00:27:31,510 --> 00:27:33,590
- Don't hang up, please. It's important--
- [beeps]

349
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:38,150
It was Isaac.

350
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:41,550
He needs to stop calling.

351
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:43,430
[disquieting music plays]

352
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:52,070
[Sam] It's okay. I'll keep you safe.

353
00:27:52,150 --> 00:27:53,950
You never have to be frightened
of me, Rosie.

354
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:14,270
[leaves crunch underfoot]

355
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:16,430
Oh, fuck! Oh, fuck.

356
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,470
Sam, is that you?

357
00:28:21,550 --> 00:28:23,030
- There he is.
- [Mason gasps]

358
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:25,270
[both chuckle]

359
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:26,630
Where have you been?

360
00:28:26,710 --> 00:28:27,790
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

361
00:28:27,870 --> 00:28:30,190
I thought I'd be back ages ago, but…

362
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:33,790
- My God. You made it.
- [laughs]

363
00:28:33,870 --> 00:28:34,990
[sighs happily]

364
00:28:37,110 --> 00:28:38,390
[Sam] Mmm.

365
00:28:40,710 --> 00:28:41,670
So, uh…

366
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:42,910
[Mason chuckles]

367
00:28:43,710 --> 00:28:46,750
How was the… the crossing? Were you sick?

368
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:49,110
No. It was-- It was fine, actually.

369
00:28:49,190 --> 00:28:50,070
Quite calm.

370
00:28:50,150 --> 00:28:51,070
[softly] Good.

371
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:54,910
- Fucking hell.
- [both laugh]

372
00:28:54,990 --> 00:28:57,750
When the fuck did you grow up
to be twice the size of me?

373
00:28:57,830 --> 00:29:01,550
I can't get over the size of you.
God, you look so different.

374
00:29:01,630 --> 00:29:04,430
I know. Well, you too, as well.
Look at you.

375
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:05,710
[Mason chuckles]

376
00:29:06,590 --> 00:29:07,630
[sighs]

377
00:29:07,710 --> 00:29:09,510
You know, I was, um…

378
00:29:10,390 --> 00:29:12,750
I was trying to work it out, uh…

379
00:29:13,750 --> 00:29:16,350
the last time
we would have seen each other.

380
00:29:17,670 --> 00:29:18,910
Do you remember?

381
00:29:19,950 --> 00:29:20,830
Family day?

382
00:29:21,430 --> 00:29:23,470
[chuckles]

383
00:29:23,550 --> 00:29:25,110
God. The prison?

384
00:29:25,190 --> 00:29:26,230
Yeah.

385
00:29:26,310 --> 00:29:27,910
Jesus.

386
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:29,750
I was 15 then.

387
00:29:30,510 --> 00:29:32,390
I was the oldest one there, as well.

388
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:35,070
All those kids running around, 
and they had fucking face paint out.

389
00:29:35,150 --> 00:29:37,590
- [laughs]
- Like, come on.

390
00:29:37,670 --> 00:29:39,070
[sighs]

391
00:29:39,150 --> 00:29:42,230
Then, obviously, 
they move you over to England.

392
00:29:44,150 --> 00:29:45,150
Yeah.

393
00:29:47,870 --> 00:29:49,230
But you're here now.

394
00:29:50,030 --> 00:29:51,110
Yeah.

395
00:29:54,950 --> 00:29:58,510
Ah, fucking hell, Mase.
I've missed you, man.

396
00:30:00,670 --> 00:30:02,630
I thought about you
all the time, you know.

397
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:03,590
[chuckles]

398
00:30:03,670 --> 00:30:07,310
- You know, how you've been and, you know--
- [groans] No, not there.

399
00:30:07,990 --> 00:30:09,310
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

400
00:30:10,990 --> 00:30:12,590
[Sam] Ah, Jesus Christ.

401
00:30:12,670 --> 00:30:14,150
[Mason] I know, I know.

402
00:30:14,790 --> 00:30:17,150
- Bet they really went to town on you?
- Yeah.

403
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:21,950
It won't stop, either.

404
00:30:22,030 --> 00:30:24,670
Messages and threats.

405
00:30:26,670 --> 00:30:28,510
Just ignore them, all right?

406
00:30:28,590 --> 00:30:31,710
And turn the location off on your phone.

407
00:30:33,870 --> 00:30:36,750
You're safe here. I swear.

408
00:30:37,310 --> 00:30:39,390
[gentle solemn music plays]

409
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:41,830
Sam, what is this place?

410
00:30:43,150 --> 00:30:45,150
[geese honk]

411
00:30:50,270 --> 00:30:52,390
Just remember to be quiet, okay?

412
00:30:58,510 --> 00:30:59,430
[softly] We're good.

413
00:31:00,950 --> 00:31:03,110
- Just head up to the back of the garden.
- Okay.

414
00:31:10,030 --> 00:31:12,550
[Mrs. Phillips sniffs]
What time did you get in?

415
00:31:13,590 --> 00:31:15,470
Five. Half five.

416
00:31:16,150 --> 00:31:18,270
Well, she's at peace now.

417
00:31:26,230 --> 00:31:27,750
Adam couldn't do it.

418
00:31:29,310 --> 00:31:31,910
Couldn't sit with her
in the darkest valley.

419
00:31:33,910 --> 00:31:35,750
And you know why, don't you?

420
00:31:37,190 --> 00:31:40,190
'Cause it shouldn't have been him.
It should have been…

421
00:31:43,070 --> 00:31:44,790
Seventeen years.

422
00:31:45,910 --> 00:31:48,990
Seventeen years next month
since we cast him out.

423
00:31:50,830 --> 00:31:52,190
Our Matthew.

424
00:31:53,830 --> 00:31:56,430
- Our "gift of God."
- I know why we called him that.

425
00:31:59,550 --> 00:32:01,710
I thought he'd see the light, 
I thought he'd come back--

426
00:32:01,790 --> 00:32:02,630
No, no.

427
00:32:02,710 --> 00:32:04,950
You can't-- You can't do this to me.

428
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:09,670
Expect me to listen to you
when I'm not allowed to breathe his name?

429
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:10,870
No.

430
00:32:15,390 --> 00:32:17,110
Coward's all you are.

431
00:32:18,430 --> 00:32:20,430
Numbing yourself in the bottle.

432
00:32:23,070 --> 00:32:24,870
I have to live with the pain.

433
00:32:30,990 --> 00:32:32,070
[chickens cluck]

434
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:33,590
[Rosie] Grace, this is Mason.

435
00:32:33,670 --> 00:32:35,150
Sam's brother.

436
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:37,550
He's just here for a wash.

437
00:32:38,150 --> 00:32:39,550
I only have a bucket.

438
00:32:41,630 --> 00:32:44,070
Mr. Phillips is waiting
for us at the mill.

439
00:32:44,150 --> 00:32:45,270
Architects are here today.

440
00:32:45,350 --> 00:32:47,070
[doorbell rings]

441
00:32:47,150 --> 00:32:49,190
[tense droning music plays]

442
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:57,870
[door opens]

443
00:32:57,950 --> 00:32:59,230
[Rosie] Isaac, you can't be here.

444
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:01,390
[Isaac] I've been trying Adam, 
he won't speak to me.

445
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:03,870
Look, that man he hired at the sawmill, 
he's dangerous.

446
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:06,790
I'm begging you, 
don't let him near you or the kids.

447
00:33:08,990 --> 00:33:11,870
Hey, Adam. Just listen.
That man, you don't know who he is.

448
00:33:11,950 --> 00:33:13,270
I know exactly who he is.

449
00:33:13,910 --> 00:33:15,510
- Yeah?
- And he's gone.

450
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:17,310
He's on the run.

451
00:33:17,390 --> 00:33:19,150
- What do you--
- I don't know where. Don't ask.

452
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:20,830
- You need to leave.
- Just let me explain.

453
00:33:20,910 --> 00:33:23,190
- You need to leave my property. Leave!
- Adam!

454
00:33:23,870 --> 00:33:24,950
You are disavowed!

455
00:33:25,990 --> 00:33:27,470
Corinthians, Chapter 5.

456
00:33:27,550 --> 00:33:29,990
"Cast out the sinners from among you."

457
00:33:31,670 --> 00:33:33,310
[sweeping dramatic music plays]

458
00:33:57,990 --> 00:33:58,990
[Sam] Rosie.

459
00:34:02,510 --> 00:34:04,030
Are you okay?

460
00:34:04,110 --> 00:34:05,630
What did you do?

461
00:34:08,110 --> 00:34:10,350
What? You know what I did.

462
00:34:10,429 --> 00:34:12,630
No. You said it was
just a fight over a girl.

463
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:14,389
What did you really do?

464
00:34:15,310 --> 00:34:17,550
Isaac told me that you were dangerous.

465
00:34:17,630 --> 00:34:19,790
That I shouldn't let you near me.
Why would he say that?

466
00:34:19,870 --> 00:34:21,270
- Rosie--
- [Adam] Ready.

467
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:23,230
Time to go.

468
00:34:27,790 --> 00:34:29,190
- Rosie, I--
- [Adam] Sam!

469
00:34:33,510 --> 00:34:35,630
[footsteps recede]

470
00:34:36,790 --> 00:34:38,750
[truck engine starts]

471
00:34:39,590 --> 00:34:41,510
- I'll see you after work, all right?
- Yeah.

472
00:34:43,310 --> 00:34:46,190
Uh… Actually, Mase.

473
00:34:46,270 --> 00:34:47,710
Uh, I need your help.

474
00:34:48,550 --> 00:34:49,630
Keep an eye out for me.

475
00:34:50,670 --> 00:34:52,830
- On what?
- Everything.

476
00:34:54,230 --> 00:34:55,909
My eyes and ears, okay?

477
00:34:56,550 --> 00:34:57,750
Yeah.

478
00:35:03,230 --> 00:35:04,430
[door closes]

479
00:35:05,310 --> 00:35:06,230
[truck door closes]

480
00:35:06,310 --> 00:35:07,710
[truck drives away]

481
00:35:09,070 --> 00:35:10,910
Top of the stairs. On the left.

482
00:35:10,990 --> 00:35:12,030
Thank you.

483
00:35:20,870 --> 00:35:22,110
[door closes]

484
00:35:27,670 --> 00:35:29,070
[cell phone chimes]

485
00:35:29,150 --> 00:35:31,870
[shower running]

486
00:35:31,950 --> 00:35:33,950
[menacing ethereal music plays]

487
00:35:42,950 --> 00:35:45,150
[shower continues running]

488
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:55,230
[chimes]

489
00:35:55,830 --> 00:35:57,830
[music intensifies]

490
00:36:11,710 --> 00:36:13,190
[bittersweet music plays]

491
00:36:19,790 --> 00:36:20,910
[door opens]

492
00:36:20,990 --> 00:36:23,070
What are you doing with my stuff?

493
00:36:26,950 --> 00:36:28,150
Who did that to you?

494
00:36:32,550 --> 00:36:34,590
- Was it Sam?
- 'Course not.

495
00:36:35,390 --> 00:36:38,710
My brother loves me. [scoffs]
He'd do anything to defend me.

496
00:36:39,310 --> 00:36:40,670
So who's looking for you?

497
00:36:40,750 --> 00:36:42,750
[tense music plays]

498
00:36:44,950 --> 00:36:45,910
You.

499
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:48,070
Your brother.

500
00:36:49,070 --> 00:36:51,470
People are looking for you both. Why?

501
00:36:51,550 --> 00:36:53,230
No, they're-- they're-- they're not.

502
00:36:59,710 --> 00:37:01,350
The police are looking for Sam.

503
00:37:02,430 --> 00:37:03,950
They were here yesterday.

504
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:10,190
I saw a message on your phone. A threat.

505
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:12,590
[sighs] No. No.

506
00:37:13,790 --> 00:37:15,070
[Mason's breath trembles]

507
00:37:15,150 --> 00:37:16,670
Mason, is this about the girl?

508
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:19,270
What?

509
00:37:20,670 --> 00:37:22,550
Sorry. I don't mean to pry.

510
00:37:22,630 --> 00:37:26,110
It's just, everyone's saying
a lot of things about Sam.

511
00:37:26,190 --> 00:37:29,390
And I've only known him a short while, 
but he's been really kind.

512
00:37:29,470 --> 00:37:30,310
And he is.

513
00:37:30,910 --> 00:37:32,070
He is kind.

514
00:37:34,550 --> 00:37:36,550
Trying to make him out
to be some sort of a monster.

515
00:37:38,190 --> 00:37:39,790
That girl and everything.

516
00:37:40,550 --> 00:37:42,590
It wasn't even his fault, you know.

517
00:37:43,510 --> 00:37:45,910
She was the one trying to leave him.

518
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:48,590
[music intensifies]

519
00:37:52,990 --> 00:37:54,590
Why don't you get dry?

520
00:37:54,670 --> 00:37:56,230
I'll put the kettle on.

521
00:37:56,910 --> 00:37:58,470
[music turns suspenseful]

522
00:38:18,830 --> 00:38:21,350
- [Isaac] Anything you say, boss.
- [Charley] Boss? [laughs]

523
00:38:22,350 --> 00:38:23,710
[cell phone rings]

524
00:38:25,190 --> 00:38:26,750
Hello, Elite Garden Sheds.

525
00:38:26,830 --> 00:38:27,990
[Rosie] Isaac.

526
00:38:28,070 --> 00:38:30,790
That man, Sam Carter, he's still here.

527
00:38:30,870 --> 00:38:32,390
What? Rosie, Adam said he'd left.

528
00:38:32,470 --> 00:38:34,550
- No, he lied.
- Rosie?

529
00:38:34,630 --> 00:38:37,190
Please. Please, I need to know
what you know about him.

530
00:38:37,270 --> 00:38:39,350
He's not Sam Carter.
His name's Sam Devlin.

531
00:38:40,230 --> 00:38:42,110
He's dangerous, Rosie.
Please, get away from him.

532
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:44,510
- [clattering]
- Rosie, are you listening?

533
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:46,790
- [Mason] What's that you're drawing?
- Rosie?

534
00:38:46,870 --> 00:38:48,550
I can't really talk.

535
00:38:49,070 --> 00:38:49,990
Where are you?

536
00:38:50,070 --> 00:38:51,910
I'm at work with Charley.

537
00:38:54,030 --> 00:38:56,790
Meet me at the playground.
Isaac, be quick.

538
00:38:57,670 --> 00:38:59,110
[phone clatters softly on base]

539
00:39:00,750 --> 00:39:02,990
Grace wants you to put this on the fridge.

540
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:13,230
Grace? Get your coat.

541
00:39:13,310 --> 00:39:14,950
We're going to see your gran.

542
00:39:15,590 --> 00:39:17,630
[Adam] This is very exciting.

543
00:39:17,710 --> 00:39:21,270
And this? This, what you've done
is so impressive.

544
00:39:21,350 --> 00:39:23,390
And we, of course, the-- the Harrisons, 

545
00:39:23,470 --> 00:39:26,190
we'll be providing
all of the prefabricated elements.

546
00:39:26,270 --> 00:39:28,430
Eh, you've found your voice now, have you?

547
00:39:29,390 --> 00:39:30,670
- Please, Mr. Phillips.
- Eh?

548
00:39:31,790 --> 00:39:33,990
And what does that mean
in terms of lead time?

549
00:39:34,070 --> 00:39:36,550
Lead? You're asking the wrong fella, love.

550
00:39:38,030 --> 00:39:41,070
Sam, phone call for you. It's a Mason.

551
00:39:42,230 --> 00:39:43,270
Thanks.

552
00:39:45,430 --> 00:39:47,350
Shouldn't be more
than three or four weeks, once--

553
00:39:47,430 --> 00:39:50,870
Perfect. Let me show you…
[continues indistinctly]

554
00:39:50,950 --> 00:39:52,910
[Adam] Yes. Yeah, exactly.

555
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:54,830
Mason. What is it?

556
00:39:56,150 --> 00:39:58,230
[Adam] So, we checked our stocks, 
and we're actually…

557
00:39:58,310 --> 00:39:59,310
[Sam] Where?

558
00:40:00,430 --> 00:40:01,710
Where's she meeting him?

559
00:40:05,870 --> 00:40:07,230
[phone clatters on base]

560
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:14,870
[woman] Have you had any more thoughts
about rainwater harvesting?

561
00:40:15,750 --> 00:40:18,230
"Do any of the worthless idols
bring rain?"

562
00:40:19,550 --> 00:40:22,630
"Do the heavens alone bring down showers?"

563
00:40:22,710 --> 00:40:23,670
- Eh?
- Jeremiah.

564
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:24,790
- [woman] Mm-hmm.
- Oh!

565
00:40:24,870 --> 00:40:26,750
Why don't I give Mr. Phillips
a lift home, huh?

566
00:40:28,030 --> 00:40:30,190
- I'll take him home. Don't worry.
- Thank you.

567
00:40:30,270 --> 00:40:31,550
[mocking] "Thank you."

568
00:40:31,630 --> 00:40:33,350
- [laughs]
- It's all right.

569
00:40:33,430 --> 00:40:36,390
[Mr. Phillips laughs loudly]

570
00:40:40,310 --> 00:40:41,910
[Sam] Come on, Mr. Phillips.

571
00:40:43,070 --> 00:40:44,070
[laughs]

572
00:40:48,950 --> 00:40:50,070
[footsteps approach]

573
00:40:53,750 --> 00:40:56,870
[music turns serene and fades]

574
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:05,790
There, you see?

575
00:41:06,510 --> 00:41:09,590
Mrs. Dawson has finished
with her old, worn-out body.

576
00:41:11,470 --> 00:41:13,550
But God hasn't finished with her soul.

577
00:41:15,430 --> 00:41:17,550
- So will you take us to the park?
- I can't.

578
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:19,350
I can't just drop everything.

579
00:41:19,430 --> 00:41:20,790
I've got Bible club.

580
00:41:21,470 --> 00:41:23,470
[forlorn music plays]

581
00:41:25,910 --> 00:41:27,510
[breathes deeply]

582
00:42:05,430 --> 00:42:07,430
[children play and chatter indistinctly]

583
00:42:19,070 --> 00:42:20,910
Thank you for doing this.

584
00:42:24,710 --> 00:42:26,510
It's not like I have a choice.

585
00:42:52,750 --> 00:42:54,750
[turn signal clicks]

586
00:43:05,190 --> 00:43:07,190
[suspenseful music plays]

587
00:43:29,230 --> 00:43:31,510
[engine revs]

588
00:43:33,350 --> 00:43:34,270
[horn honks]

589
00:43:44,230 --> 00:43:45,710
[tires squeal]

590
00:43:49,590 --> 00:43:51,670
- [Sam exclaims]
- [horn honks]

591
00:43:52,790 --> 00:43:54,510
- [Mr. Phillips] No! No!
- [tires squeal]

592
00:43:55,950 --> 00:43:57,310
For the love of God!

593
00:43:57,390 --> 00:43:58,430
[groans]

594
00:43:59,150 --> 00:44:00,670
Grace, be careful.

595
00:44:01,190 --> 00:44:03,190
[suspenseful music continues]

596
00:44:07,110 --> 00:44:09,110
[engine revs]

597
00:44:16,630 --> 00:44:20,150
- [Mrs. Phillips] There we go, Grace.
- Faster! Faster!

598
00:44:22,150 --> 00:44:23,990
[tires squeal]

599
00:44:30,390 --> 00:44:32,750
Faster! Faster!

600
00:44:35,470 --> 00:44:37,470
[music intensifies]

601
00:44:43,950 --> 00:44:45,110
[music stops abruptly]

602
00:44:53,190 --> 00:44:55,190
[alarm wails, horn blares]

603
00:45:01,350 --> 00:45:02,550
[engine turns off]

604
00:45:10,230 --> 00:45:12,230
[breathes heavily]

605
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:16,230
Uh…

606
00:45:19,150 --> 00:45:20,590
[gasps]

607
00:45:29,830 --> 00:45:32,470
["Send His Love to Me" by PJ Harvey plays]

608
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:48,750
♪ Lover had to leave me ♪

609
00:45:48,830 --> 00:45:52,430
♪ 'Cross the desert plain ♪

610
00:45:52,510 --> 00:45:56,350
♪ Turned to me, his lady ♪

611
00:45:56,430 --> 00:46:00,150
♪ Tell me, "Lover, wait" ♪

612
00:46:00,230 --> 00:46:04,710
♪ I'm calling Jesus, please ♪

613
00:46:07,950 --> 00:46:12,670
♪ Send his love to me ♪

614
00:46:14,830 --> 00:46:19,030
♪ Oh, wind and rain, they haunt me ♪

615
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:23,230
♪ Look to the north and pray ♪

616
00:46:23,310 --> 00:46:27,070
♪ Send me, please, his kisses ♪

617
00:46:27,150 --> 00:46:30,910
♪ Send them home today ♪

618
00:46:30,990 --> 00:46:35,590
♪ I'm begging, Jesus, please ♪
